The '''Lagos Seafood Festival''' is an annual event in [[Lagos, Nigeria|Lagos]]. The first edition of the festival held on 10 November 2012 at the [[Eko Hotel and Suites]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2012/11/lagos-boosts-local-fish-production/|title =Lagos boosts local fish production|date=2 November 2012|author=Olasunkanmi Akoni|publisher = The Vanguard|accessdate = 28 January 2016}}</ref>
The festival is aimed at promoting [[seafood]] cuisine culture, local fish production and stimulating investment opportunities in relation to [[aquaculture]] and [[fisheries]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://dailypost.ng/2012/11/11/governor-fashola-flags-first-ever-lagos-sea-food-festival/|title = Governor Fashola flags first ever Lagos Seafood Festival|publisher = Daily Post|accessdate = 28 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mynewswatchtimesng.com/lagos-seafood-festival-stimulate-investment-potential-commissioner/|title =Lagos Seafood Festival to stimulate investment potential – Commissioner|author=Boldwin Anugwara |date = 2 December 2013|publisher=Newswatch|location=Nigeria |accessdate = 28 January 2016}}</ref>
