{{About|the upcoming History series|the primary title of the NBC anthology series|Project U.F.O.}} {{Missing information|production, additional casting|date=September 2018}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Project Blue Book | image = | caption = | genre = {{Plainlist| * [[Historical period drama]] * [[Science fiction]] }} | creator = | writer = | director = | starring = {{Plainlist| * [[Aidan Gillen]] * [[Laura Mennell]] * [[Michael Harney]] * [[Ksenia Solo]] * [[Michael Malarkey]] }} | composer = | country = United States | language = English | num_seasons = <!--1--> | num_episodes = <!--10--> | list_episodes = | executive_producer = {{Plainlist| * [[Robert Zemeckis]] * David O'Leary * Sean Jablonski }} | producer = | location = [[Vancouver, British Columbia]] <!--Source: http://www.whatsfilming.ca/inproduction/ --> | cinematography = | editor = | camera = | runtime = | company = {{Plainlist| * [[A&E Networks#A&E Studios|A&E Studios]] * Compari Entertainment * [[History (U.S. TV channel)|History]] * [[ImageMovers]] }} | network = [[History (U.S. TV network)|History]] | picture_format = | audio_format = | first_aired = <!-- Only insert the date after it has happened. See [[Template:Infobox television]] --> | last_aired = | related = | website = https://www.history.com/shows/project-blue-book | website_title = Official website }} '''''Project Blue Book''''' is an upcoming American [[science fiction]] [[Historical period drama|drama]] television series, scheduled to premiere on [[History (U.S. TV network)|History]] January 8, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pedersen |first1=Erik |title=‘Project Blue Book’: History Reveals Premiere Date & Trailer For Robert Zemeckis’ UFO Drama Series |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/project-blue-book-premiere-date-trailer-history-channel-ufo-drama-series-1202477171/ |website=Deadline |accessdate=5 October 2018 |date=5 October 2018}}</ref> The main role of [[J. Allen Hynek|Josef Allen Hynek]] is played by [[Aidan Gillen]], and the series will consist of ten episodes.<ref name="denofgeek">{{cite web |url=http://www.denofgeek.com/us/tv/blue-book/268549/aidan-gillen-to-star-in-robert-zemeckis-ufo-series-blue-book|title=Aidan Gillen to Star in Robert Zemeckis UFO Series Blue Book|date=October 26, 2017 |website=Den of Geek!|accessdate=October 27, 2017 }}</ref><ref name="usatoday">{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2017/05/25/blue-book-series-history-channel-robert-zemeckis/102147536/|title='Blue Book' value: History picks up UFO drama from Robert Zemeckis|date=May 25, 2017 |website=USA Today|accessdate=October 27, 2017|first=Jayme|last=Deerwester}}</ref> The series is based on the real-life [[Project Blue Book]].
==Premise== The series revolves around secret U.S. Air Force investigations into supposed UFO encounters and unexplained phenomenon, undertaken by astrophysicist, and eventual ufologist, Josef Allen Hynek in the 1950s and 1960s.<ref name="denofgeek"/><ref name="usatoday"/>
==Cast and characters== * [[Aidan Gillen]] as [[J. Allen Hynek|Josef Allen Hynek]]<ref name="denofgeek"/> * [[Michael Malarkey]] as Captain Michael Quinn<ref name="Deadline3">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2017/12/blue-book-michael-malarkey-cast-robert-zemeckis-produced-ufo-series-history-1202222754/|title=‘Blue Book’: Michael Malarkey Joins Robert Zemeckis-Produced UFO Series At History |first=Denise|last=Petski |date=December 8, 2017 |website=Deadline Hollywood |access-date=December 8, 2017}}</ref> * [[Laura Mennell]] as Mimi Hynek<ref name="deadline">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2017/11/blue-book-laura-mennell-cast-robert-zemeckis-produced-ufo-series-history-1202204382/|title=‘Blue Book’: Laura Mennell To Star In UFO Series At History |first=Nellie|last=Andreeva |date=November 8, 2017 |website=Deadline Hollywood |access-date=November 9, 2017}}</ref> *[[Michael Harney]] as General Hugh Valentine<ref name="Deadline2">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2017/11/blue-book-michael-harney-ksenia-solo-cast-robert-zemeckis-produced-ufo-series-history-1202213310/|title=‘Blue Book’: Michael Harney & Ksenia Solo Join Robert Zemeckis-Produced UFO Series At History |first=Denise|last=Petski |date=November 21, 2017 |website=Deadline Hollywood |access-date=November 21, 2017}}</ref> * [[Ksenia Solo]] as Susie Miller<ref name="Deadline2"/>
